<title>USER-MESSAGE</title>
</head>

<body>
	<h3>
	<i>I display a message in a dialogue box.</i></h3>
	<p>
	<font color="gray" size="2">Begin micro-behaviour</font></p>
	<p>
	<b>USER-MESSAGE</b></p>
	<font color="gray" size="2">Begin NetLogo code:</font><pre>substitute-text-area-for columns: 78 rows: 5 dialogue-message &quot;Click on the GO button to run this model. &quot;        
user-message
  dialogue-message</pre>
	<font color="gray" size="2">End NetLogo code</font><h2>Variants</h2>
	<p>Edit the text of the message. You can use NetLogo's word function to 
	construct dynamic messages. E.g. (word &quot;The population at time &quot; time &quot; is &quot; 
	count all-individuals).</p>
	<h2>Related Behaviours</h2>
	<p><a href="ADD-MESSAGE.html">ADD-MESSAGE</a> adds a custom message to the output 
area.</p>
	<h2>How this works</h2>
	<p>It calls the NetLogo 
	<a target="_blank" href="http://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#user-message">
	user-message</a>
	procedure to add text to the output area (by 
	default at the bottom of the application).</p>
	<h2>History</h2>
	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn.</p>

</body>

